<p>Using the <em><a href="https://thl.okstate.edu">Take Home Labs</a></em> from Oklahoma State University, we have developed our very own motor modeling and control demonstration kit. The open loop modeling and control labs were included as a first in the CSE 361 course offering of Winter 2021.</p>
<p>The kit requires the following components:</p>
<ul>
<li>Arduino Mega 2560</li>
<li>Arduino motor control shield (any)</li>
<li>Any DC motor with known gear ratio</li>
<li>Motor encoder (preferrably built-in with the motor)</li>
<li>MATLAB and Simulink Student Suite with Arduino Support Add-ons</li>
</ul>
<p>To work with different motor types, different 3D printed mounts were prepared. Here are a few:</p>
<p><img src="assets\blog-0db385d7.png" alt="Mount for goBilda Motor and Mega" width="300"></p>
